# Colors

Only use the color variables defined in `app/globals.css`. Never use raw hex, rgb, hsl values, or arbitrary Tailwind color classes (e.g. `text-blue-500`, `bg-[#1D4ED8]`).

## Available colors

| Variable | Tailwind class | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `--background` | `bg-background` / `text-background` | Page background |
| `--text` | `text-text` | Body text |
| `--primary` | `bg-primary` / `text-primary` | Primary actions, links |
| `--accent` | `bg-accent` / `text-accent` | Highlights, badges |
| `--secondary` | `bg-secondary` / `text-secondary` | Subtle backgrounds |
| `--hover` | `bg-hover` / `text-hover` | Hover states |

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<button className="bg-primary text-background hover:bg-hover">Click</button>
<p className="text-text">Hello</p>

// ❌ BAD — raw color value
<button className="bg-[#1D4ED8] text-white">Click</button>
<p className="text-slate-800">Hello</p>
```

```css
/* ✅ GOOD */
color: var(--text);
background: var(--primary);

/* ❌ BAD */
color: #1E293B;
background: #1D4ED8;
```
